|CKBThe Confidence: A Charlatan's First Honest Document|000

Welcome to the Confidence. The name is impressive, the paperwork is
questionable, and your cloak has more pockets than anyone remembers sewing.

Charlatans win by making the wrong thing look certain. Some talk a foe into
forgetting the fight. Some turn corpse ash into something fizzy and legally
distinct from medicine. Some improve weapons with substances best handled by
someone else. The wisest learn a little of all three and deny everything.

Your reputation is measured in Charlatan Rank and guild XP. Worthy fights and
boss victories earn guild XP. Each Rank after the first gives you one road
point until you have earned thirty, enough to complete all three roads:

  Misdirection - lies, openings, thrown voices, and weaponized confidence
  Volatility    - unstable brews, additives, ash, and regrettable chemistry
  Contraband    - loaded weapons, stretched poison, and excellent excuses

Use:

  chskills [available]   Inspect the tricks in your cloak
  gscore charlatan       See Rank, guild XP, roads, and profession skills
  croads train <road>    Spend an uninvested road point
  schemes                Inspect Rank 35+ cons and active cloak notes
  charlhelp commands     Read the full command ledger
  charlatan <message>    Work the guild line

Every new Charlatan can confuse a mark and suckerpunch the opening. Roads add
specialties after Rank 1; they do not make you earn your first unfair fight.
At Rank 35 and every five Ranks through 100, Drina opens another horizontal
scheme. You can learn every scheme eventually, but only a few cloak notes can
be active at once.

Alchemy, Herbalism, and Smithing are learned through their own trades. Your
roads decide what sort of rascal you are; those professions decide whether
you can safely execute the technical parts. "Safely" is used generously.

The old Alchemist and Illusionist focus ledgers are closed. If an ancient
page promises flying potions, poison darts, or a personal shadow army, check
the date, check your pockets, and use 'chskills'.
